               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1485" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1485" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1485" type="surname" value="LAMBERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1485" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LAMBERT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carver, and live in Pitt-street, Old Kent-road. The prisoner was my journeyman for two or three months—I missed this property on the 10th of May, from a chest of drawers in the front parlour—the prisoner went away that day, without giving me notice—I paid him at the end of every week, and this was on Monday morning—I had left him at work—I found him at the station-house, with my coat and trowsers on—I examined, and missed a sovereign and fifteen shillings from the top drawer, and the clothes—he behaved very well while with me.</p>
